@endnode

@node Introduction
The program is a converter from an IFF-Brush with 270x128 with 4 Bitplanes.
You can draw a picture with DPaint and save a brush with 270x128. A default
picture with the colour specification is called Screen.IFF. You load it in
DPaint and paint in the grey area. This area has the size of 270x128.
If you don“t use it, the program will fail!!! 
USAGE : IFF2RGS <infile> <outfile>
        <infile>  : the IFF-Brush with 270x128x4
        <outfile> : the name of the RGS-File, which will be created
@endnode

